<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="1295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1295">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2643</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-17T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3101. Your 4001, June 15, 2 p. m. In order to make position of Department
                            definite, it would be better if it could state that Doctor <persName corresp="#p_TDAE1">Taylor</persName>’s report was published with
                            consent of German authorities. Ascertain whether German authorities will
                            give such consent and report earliest possible moment.<note n="1" xml:id="d1295fn1">In his telegram No. 4050, June 26, 1916 [received
                                June 27], the Ambassador stated: “German Government has no objection
                                to publication Doctor <persName corresp="#p_TDAE1">Taylor</persName>’s milk report.” It was accordingly given to the
                                press and printed for distribution to inquirers on the
                                subject.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>